  "prompt": "Why wasn't John Williams hired to write the soundtrack to Rogue One?",
  "response": "John Williams, who had previously composed the iconic scores for the main episodes of the Star Wars saga, was not hired to write the soundtrack for \"Rogue One: A Star Wars Story\" due to scheduling conflicts and other commitments. Williams was busy with other projects around the time \"Rogue One\" was in development. As a result, Lucasfilm turned to Michael Giacchino, a renowned composer known for his work on films like \"Up,\" \"The Incredibles,\" and several other major film scores. Giacchino was able to bring his own unique touch to the film while still honoring the musical legacy of the Star Wars franchise.",
